@startuml SCRUM-60 Search Sort

title Buyer Sort Search Results (SCRUM-60)\n(sortBy whitelist → fixed ORDER BY in DAO)

actor Buyer as U
participant "Browser\n(search.jsp)" as B
participant "SearchServlet\nGET /search" as S
participant "SearchSort\n(enum whitelist)" as SS
participant "SearchDAO" as DAO
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

U -> B : Select sort option from dropdown\n(e.g. "Ending soonest")
B -> S : GET /search?q=watch&sortBy=endingSoon\n         [&filters…]

activate S

note right of S
  <b>SCRUM-349 – sortBy security:</b>
  sortBy validated via SearchSort.fromParam()
  Whitelist: newest | endingSoon | priceLow | priceHigh
  Unknown / blank / SQL injection string → DEFAULT (newest)
  Never concatenated raw into SQL — enum maps to
  hard-coded ORDER BY fragments only.
end note

S -> S : validate keyword, parse filters (SCRUM-59)
S -> SS : fromParam("endingSoon")
activate SS
SS --> S : SearchSort.ENDING_SOON
deactivate SS

S -> DAO : search(keyword, category, filter,\n         SearchSort.ENDING_SOON, page, size)
activate DAO

note right of DAO
  <b>ORDER BY mapping (SCRUM-348) — fixed strings only:</b>
  NEWEST      → ORDER BY a.date_created DESC
  ENDING_SOON → ORDER BY a.date_end ASC
  PRICE_LOW   → ORDER BY current_price ASC
  PRICE_HIGH  → ORDER BY current_price DESC

  sort.orderBySimple() or sort.orderByWrapped()
  depending on whether price-filter subquery wrap is used.
  No user input reaches the ORDER BY clause.
end note

DAO -> DAO : buildInnerFromWhere(keyword, category, filter)
DAO -> DAO : append sort.orderBySimple()\n  → "ORDER BY a.date_end ASC"
DAO -> DB : SELECT … FROM auction a …\n  WHERE … (all params bound via PreparedStatement)\n  ORDER BY a.date_end ASC\n  LIMIT ? OFFSET ?
DB --> DAO : sorted result rows
DAO --> S : List<SearchResultItem>
deactivate DAO

S -> S : setAttribute("sortBy", "endingSoon")
S -> B : forward search.jsp
deactivate S

B -> U : Render results in chosen sort order\n  Sort dropdown + pagination preserve sortBy

== Invalid sortBy (SCRUM-349) ==

U -> B : Manipulate URL: sortBy='; DROP TABLE bids;--
B -> S : GET /search?q=phone&sortBy='; DROP TABLE bids;--
activate S
S -> SS : fromParam("'; DROP TABLE bids;--")
SS --> S : SearchSort.DEFAULT (NEWEST)
note right of SS : Unknown value → DEFAULT\nInjection string never reaches SQL
S -> DAO : search(…, SearchSort.NEWEST, …)
DAO -> DB : … ORDER BY a.date_created DESC …
S -> B : forward (sorted by newest — no error)
deactivate S

@enduml
